! What it is

A keyboard-driven, ''cascading'' command palette engine. The user opens it with one hotkey, types to filter a menu, and uses ''→ / Space / Esc / Enter'' to navigate stages of progressively narrower choices (Esc walks one stage back; Shift-Esc closes from any depth).

The novelty (vs. flat palettes like souk21/commandpalette or VS Code's Cmd-P) is that picking an item ''drills'' into a new stage — and that stage's items can be follow-up actions on the picked entity, or further drills into related sets. The result feels like Raycast on macOS, but powered by declarative tiddler data instead of code.

! What it gives you

* ''Generic engine'' — no domain knowledge. The same widget serves any catalogue plugin that ships ''entry'' and ''action'' tiddlers.
* ''Declarative cascades'' — extending the palette is writing one tiddler per cascade edge. No JS. No widget changes.
* ''Composable tree shapes'' — a view is a composition of ''structure layers''. Each layer declares its own `roots` + `children` filters AND can optionally chain ''axes'' (year / month / day / status / prefix — anything you can express as a derive-key filter). Axes form the top of the descent, `children` forms the recursive bottom; they're orthogonal and combine cleanly on a single layer.
* ''Filter substitution'' — `<<query>>`, `<<picked>>`, `<<parent-picked>>` available in any filter or action wikitext.
* ''Sticky context'' — pin one or more tiddlers (Space → "Pin to context", or type `+<title>` + Enter) and they appear as `<<sticky-context-list>>` / `<<sticky-context-count>>` variables exposed to every filter/action scope. Page-session only (cleared on reload). Views opt in to narrowing by referencing the variable in their layer filters AND declaring `ca-view-context-aware: yes` to paint a small badge when context is non-empty. The mechanism is generic; workflow-specific verbs (call, meeting, focus) live in sibling plugins like `rimir/worga`.
* ''Row icons'' — small footer-strip glyphs on tiddler-bearing rows surface affordances (open external URL, jump to attachment, custom actions) without crowding the name slot. ''Alt-↵'' or click on the glyph fires the primary icon. Shipped: a 🌐 icon for tiddlers carrying http/https/ftp/mailto/tel in a configurable URL field. Extensible via tiddlers tagged `$:/tags/rimir/cascade-palette/row-icon`.
* ''Keyboard-first'' — Up/Down navigate rows; Tab cycles focus //sections// (Shift-Tab jumps top↔bottom group); → drills (descend a tree container or open the action menu on a typed catalogue row); Space opens the action menu on ''any'' tiddler row whose actions match via `ca-applies` — works in tree views like ''By namespace'' / ''By parent'' / ''Hybrid'', not only in the catalogue; Enter fires; Esc walks one stage back (closes only at root from input); Shift-Esc closes from any depth. Left/Right inside the input keep normal cursor semantics.

! Catalogue plugins

The cascade engine on its own ships only a couple of generic demo entries (Search all, Recent tiddlers). The real value comes from ''catalogue plugins'' that depend on this one and ship orga-specific / domain-specific entries and actions:

* ''`rimir/orga-palette`'' — orga-data-model entry types (Persons, Projects, Tasks, Meetings, …) with per-type action menus (Open, Assigned Teams, Mark Done, …).
* (future) ''`rimir/priv-palette`'' — analogous catalogue for `private-data-model`.

! Prerequisites

* TiddlyWiki ≥ 5.4.0

